{{for|the American magazine from the 1950s|Photo (American magazine)}} {{Infobox magazine | title = Photo | logo = | logo_size = <!-- default is 180px --> | image_file = <!-- cover.jpg (omit the "file:" prefix) --> | image_size = <!-- default is 180px --> | image_alt = | image_caption = | editor = <!-- up to |editor5= --> | editor_title = <!-- up to |editor_title5= --> | previous_editor = | staff_writer = | photographer = | category = Photography | frequency = | format = | circulation = | publisher = | paid_circulation = | unpaid_circulation = | circulation_year = | total_circulation = | founder = | founded = 1960 | firstdate = <!-- {{Start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | finaldate = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | finalnumber = | company = EPMA | country = France | based = | language = French | website = {{URL|http://www.photo.fr}} | issn = 0399-8568 | oclc = }}
'''''Photo''''' is a [[France|French]] magazine about [[photography]] previously published by [[Hachette Filipacchi Médias]], and currently owned by EPMA.
==History and profile== ''Photo'' was started by Hachette Filipacchi Médias as a monthly magazine in 1960.<ref name="lyn">{{cite book|author=Lynne Warren|title=Encyclopedia of Twentieth-Century Photography|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=cFVsBgAAQBAJ&pg=PA1211|accessdate=3 January 2016|date=15 November 2005|publisher=Taylor & Francis|isbn=978-1-135-20543-0|page=1211}}</ref> It was modeled on the magazine ''American Photo''.<ref name=lyn/> The magazine is now published ten times a year.<ref>{{cite web|title=Photo magazines of the world|url=https://www.redbullphotography.com/news/photo-magazines-of-the-world|publisher=Red Bull Photography|accessdate=3 January 2016|date=21 May 2015}}</ref> It concentrates on the artistic aspects of photography, rather than technical aspects. The editorial line is tripartite: fashion/nude/[[Glamour photography|glamour]], historical images of wars/guillotines/poverty or similar, and selected journalism news photos from around the world. It is read and distributed around the world, and is known featuring naked [[supermodel|models]], colorful saturated graphic images, and its annual [[amateur]] photography [[competition|contest]]. It was sold by Hachette Filipacchi in 2011. <!-- Image with unknown copyright status removed: [[Image:416.jpg|100px|thumb|right|Cover of the 2004 "spécial amateurs" (amateur contest special issue).]] -->
An American edition was published under the name '''''Photo World''''' from 1973 to 1978.<ref>{{Cite news| issn = 0362-4331| last = Dougherty| first = Philip H.| title = Advertising: Exurban Magazine| work = The New York Times| accessdate = 2018-05-28| date = 1973-10-29| url = https://www.nytimes.com/1973/10/29/archives/a-advertising-exurban-magazine-airways-tuppence-worth-accounts-a.html}}</ref>
